The paper discusses optimal equilibria in multi-player games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the concept of a player with the power to define an equilibrium, which involves decision-making and strategic thinking, and could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the complexity of constructing equilibria, which could be related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mean-payoff games, which could be relevant to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
